{"session_id": 54, "bill_id": 18268, "bill_type": "House Bill", "bill_number": 1261, "bill_title": "restrict public corporations from making purchases from any retailer that fails to collect and remit sales and use taxes.", "sponsors": [{"legislator_profile_id": 2834, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2855, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 2863, "is_prime": false}], "keywords": ["Public Property, Purchases and Contracts", "Sales Taxes", "Taxation"], "audio": [{"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-06T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/hta17hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-06T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/hta17hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-06T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/hta17hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-13T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/hta22hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-13T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/hta22hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-13T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/hta22hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-13T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/hta22hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-18T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/hou24hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-18T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/hou24hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-18T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/hou24hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-28T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "STA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/sta33hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-28T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "STA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/sta33hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2003-02-28T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "STA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2003/sta33hb1261a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 18268, "bill_version_id": 96403, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2003-02-03T11:36:31-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to restrict public corporations from making purchases from any retailer that fails to collect and remit sales and use taxes. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 5-18 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: No public corporation may purchase any goods or services from any retailer that meets the definition of a retailer or a retailer maintaining a place of business in the state, pursuant to subdivisions 10-46-1(8) and 10-46-1(9), if the retailer or any affiliate of the retailer fails or refuses to collect and remit the sales and use tax on all sales delivered by any means to a location within this state. The Department of Revenue shall provide a list of any retailers that fail to collect and remit the sales and use tax to the Bureau of Administration and the Bureau of Administration shall make such information available through the centralized public bid exchange. 350 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.027 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 18268, "bill_version_id": 97162, "bill_version": "House Taxation Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2003-02-13T14:46:42-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to restrict public corporations from making purchases from any retailer that fails to collect and remit sales and use taxes. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 5-18 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: No public corporation may purchase any goods or services from any retailer that meets the definition of a retailer or a retailer maintaining a place of business in the state, pursuant to subdivisions 10-46-1(8) and (9), if the retailer or any affiliate of the retailer fails or refuses to collect and remit the sales and use tax on any sale delivered by any means to a location within this state. The Department of Revenue shall provide a list to public corporations of any retailer that fails to collect and remit the sales and use tax. For the purposes of this section, the term, affiliate, is any person who directly or indirectly owns or controls, is owned or controlled by, or is under common ownership or control with, another person. No public corporation is liable for the breach of any duty required of the public corporation by the provisions of this Act if the breach, error, act, or omission is made in good faith. The provisions of this Act do not apply to any emergency purchase made pursuant to \u00a7 5-18-3.1, or to any purchase made pursuant to \u00a7 5- 18-18.1, 5-18-18.2, or 5-18-9.4, or to any contract for the construction of a new building or the remodeling or addition to an existing building or a contract for any other public improvement which involves the expenditure of twenty-five thousand dollars or more made pursuant to \u00a7 5- 18-3."}, {"bill_id": 18268, "bill_version_id": 98370, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2003-03-05T08:44:18-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 18268, "action_date": "2003-02-03T14:00:00-06:00", 